main event: Radar operators at Kirksville Air Force Station observed 6 to 12 unidentified objects on radar on September 17, 1960.
interesting points: The objects were painted as normal aircraft returns,The radar showed a descending trajectory from 27,000 ft to 23,000 ft,There were possible unusual weather conditions noted during the observation,The radar targets exhibited rapid acceleration and high speed before disappearing,No visual sightings were reported due to the rapid nature of the objects.
witness description: radar operators at Kirksville Air Force Station
